{"title_page": "Henry Daniels", "text_new": "{{For|the member of the Queensland Legislative Assembly|Henry John Daniels}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2012}}\n'''Henry Ellis Daniels''' [[Fellow of the Royal Society|FRS]]<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Cox | first1 = D. | authorlink = David Cox (statistician)| doi = 10.1098/rsbm.2003.0008 | title = Henry Ellis Daniels. 2 October 1912 - 16 April 2000 | journal = [[Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society]] | volume = 49 | pages = 133 | year = 2003 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> (2 October 1912 \u2013 16 April 2000)<ref name=obit1>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1111/1467-9884.00273 | title = Obituaries: Henry Daniels, Edwin J. Redfern | journal = Journal of the Royal Statistical Society, Series D | volume = 50 | issue = 2 | pages = 213\u2013215 | year = 2001 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> was a [[UK|British]] [[statistician]]. He was [[President of the Royal Statistical Society]] (1974\u20131975), and was awarded its [[Guy Medal]] in Gold in 1984, following a Silver medal in 1947. He became a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of London]] in 1980. The [[Parry-Daniels map]] is named after him (together with the [[England|English]] [[mathematician]] [[Bill Parry (mathematician)|Bill Parry]]).<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Whittle | first1 = P. | authorlink = Peter Whittle (mathematician)| title = A Conversation with Henry Daniels | journal = Statistical Science | volume = 8 | issue = 3 | pages = 342\u2013353 | doi = 10.1214/ss/1177010911 | year = 1993 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref><ref>{{MathGenealogy |id=57769}}</ref>\n\nDaniels' family was [[Jews|Jewish]], of [[History of the Jews in Russia|Russian]] (partly [[Poles|Polish]] and partly [[Lithuanian people|Lithuanian]]) origin.<ref name=\"odnb\">{{Cite journal | title = The Oxford Dictionary of National Biography | doi = 10.1093/ref:odnb/74126 | year = 2004 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> He was educated at [[George Heriot's School]].<ref name=\"odnb\" /> He subsequently graduated from the [[University of Edinburgh]] (M.A. Hons. 1933, Ph.D. 1943)<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Daniels|first=H. E.|date=1943|title=On the strength distribution of bundles of threads, and its asymptotic approximation|url=https://era.ed.ac.uk/handle/1842/32287|language=en}}</ref> and went on to further study at [[Clare College, Cambridge]] (B.A. 1935).<ref>{{Who's Who | surname = DANIELS | othernames = Prof. Henry Ellis | id = U177889 | type = was | volume = 2018 | edition = online}} {{subscription required}}</ref> In 1957, he became the first Professor of Mathematical Statistics at the [[University of Birmingham]].<ref name=obit1/> He stayed at the university till his retirement in 1978. After retirement, he went to Cambridge and lived there until his death.<ref>{{cite news|last=Whittle|first=Peter|title=Obituary: Henry Daniels|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2000/may/04/guardianobituaries1|accessdate=24 September 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|date=4 May 2000}}</ref>\n\nThe watchmaker [[George Daniels (watchmaker)|George Daniels]] (no relation) enlisted Daniels' help with the equations required for the design of his ''Space Traveller's Watch''.<ref name=\"obit1\" />\n\n==Selected publications by Daniels==\n*{{Cite journal | last1 = Daniels | first1 = H. E. | title = Saddlepoint Approximations in Statistics | doi = 10.1214/aoms/1177728652 | journal = The Annals of Mathematical Statistics | volume = 25 | issue = 4 | pages = 631 | year = 1954 | pmid =  | pmc = | url = http://dml.cz/bitstream/handle/10338.dmlcz/135391/Kybernetika_37-2001-1_7.pdf }}\n*{{Cite journal | last1 = Daniels | first1 = H. E. | title = Statistics in Universities--A Personal View | journal = [[Journal of the Royal Statistical Society]] | volume = 138 | issue = 1 | pages = 1\u201317 | doi = 10.2307/2345246 | year = 1975 | pmid =  | pmc = }}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n<!-- * [http://www.imstat.org/BULLETIN/july2000/node13.html IMS Bulletin: Obituary]  no longer available-->\n* [http://www.bath.ac.uk/ncuacs/guided.htm#DanielsHE Papers and biographical sketch]\n* [http://www.york.ac.uk/depts/maths/histstat/people/daniels.gif Photograph]\n* [http://www.statslab.cam.ac.uk/History/2history.html The History of the Cambridge Statistical Laboratory]\n\n{{Guy Medal}}\n{{Royal Statistical Society presidents}}\n{{FRS 1980}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniels, Henry E.}}\n[[Category:1912 births]]\n[[Category:2000 deaths]]\n[[Category:British Jews]]\n[[Category:Jewish scientists]]\n[[Category:British statisticians]]\n[[Category:British people of Polish-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:British people of Lithuanian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:British people of Russian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Clare College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Birmingham]]\n[[Category:Fellows of King's College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Royal Statistical Society]]\n[[Category:20th-century mathematicians]]\n\n\n{{UK-statistician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|the member of the Queensland Legislative Assembly|Henry John Daniels}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2012}}\n'''Henry Ellis Daniels''' [[Fellow of the Royal Society|FRS]]<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Cox | first1 = D. | authorlink = David Cox (statistician)| doi = 10.1098/rsbm.2003.0008 | title = Henry Ellis Daniels. 2 October 1912 - 16 April 2000 | journal = [[Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society]] | volume = 49 | pages = 133 | year = 2003 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> (2 October 1912 \u2013 16 April 2000)<ref name=obit1>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1111/1467-9884.00273 | title = Obituaries: Henry Daniels, Edwin J. Redfern | journal = Journal of the Royal Statistical Society, Series D | volume = 50 | issue = 2 | pages = 213\u2013215 | year = 2001 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> was a [[UK|British]] [[statistician]]. He was [[President of the Royal Statistical Society]] (1974\u20131975), and was awarded its [[Guy Medal]] in Gold in 1984, following a Silver medal in 1947. He became a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of London]] in 1980. The [[Parry-Daniels map]] is named after him (together with the [[England|English]] [[mathematician]] [[Bill Parry (mathematician)|Bill Parry]]).<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Whittle | first1 = P. | authorlink = Peter Whittle (mathematician)| title = A Conversation with Henry Daniels | journal = Statistical Science | volume = 8 | issue = 3 | pages = 342\u2013353 | doi = 10.1214/ss/1177010911 | year = 1993 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref><ref>{{MathGenealogy |id=57769}}</ref>\n\nDaniels' family was [[Jews|Jewish]], of [[History of the Jews in Russia|Russian]] (partly [[Poles|Polish]] and partly [[Lithuanian people|Lithuanian]]) origin.<ref name=\"odnb\">{{Cite journal | title = The Oxford Dictionary of National Biography | doi = 10.1093/ref:odnb/74126 | year = 2004 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> He was educated at [[George Heriot's School]].<ref name=\"odnb\" /> He subsequently graduated from the [[University of Edinburgh]] (M.A. Hons. 1933, Ph.D. 1943) and went on to further study at [[Clare College, Cambridge]] (B.A. 1935).<ref>{{Who's Who | surname = DANIELS | othernames = Prof. Henry Ellis | id = U177889 | type = was | volume = 2018 | edition = online}} {{subscription required}}</ref> In 1957, he became the first Professor of Mathematical Statistics at the [[University of Birmingham]].<ref name=obit1/> He stayed at the university till his retirement in 1978. After retirement, he went to Cambridge and lived there until his death.<ref>{{cite news|last=Whittle|first=Peter|title=Obituary: Henry Daniels|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2000/may/04/guardianobituaries1|accessdate=24 September 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|date=4 May 2000}}</ref>\n\nThe watchmaker [[George Daniels (watchmaker)|George Daniels]] (no relation) enlisted Daniels' help with the equations required for the design of his ''Space Traveller's Watch''.<ref name=\"obit1\" />\n\n==Selected publications by Daniels==\n*{{Cite journal | last1 = Daniels | first1 = H. E. | title = Saddlepoint Approximations in Statistics | doi = 10.1214/aoms/1177728652 | journal = The Annals of Mathematical Statistics | volume = 25 | issue = 4 | pages = 631 | year = 1954 | pmid =  | pmc = | url = http://dml.cz/bitstream/handle/10338.dmlcz/135391/Kybernetika_37-2001-1_7.pdf }}\n*{{Cite journal | last1 = Daniels | first1 = H. E. | title = Statistics in Universities--A Personal View | journal = [[Journal of the Royal Statistical Society]] | volume = 138 | issue = 1 | pages = 1\u201317 | doi = 10.2307/2345246 | year = 1975 | pmid =  | pmc = }}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n<!-- * [http://www.imstat.org/BULLETIN/july2000/node13.html IMS Bulletin: Obituary]  no longer available-->\n* [http://www.bath.ac.uk/ncuacs/guided.htm#DanielsHE Papers and biographical sketch]\n* [http://www.york.ac.uk/depts/maths/histstat/people/daniels.gif Photograph]\n* [http://www.statslab.cam.ac.uk/History/2history.html The History of the Cambridge Statistical Laboratory]\n\n{{Guy Medal}}\n{{Royal Statistical Society presidents}}\n{{FRS 1980}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniels, Henry E.}}\n[[Category:1912 births]]\n[[Category:2000 deaths]]\n[[Category:British Jews]]\n[[Category:Jewish scientists]]\n[[Category:British statisticians]]\n[[Category:British people of Polish-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:British people of Lithuanian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:British people of Russian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Clare College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Birmingham]]\n[[Category:Fellows of King's College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Royal Statistical Society]]\n[[Category:20th-century mathematicians]]\n\n\